.TH DEBFORGE 1 "2026" "DebForge 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
debforge \- Debian package build framework
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B debforge
.RI <command> " [options]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
DebForge is a command-line framework for building, validating,
and packaging Debian (.deb) packages using a structured workflow.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Initialize a new workspace.
.TP
.B build
Build package contents.
.TP
.B validate
Validate package structure.
.TP
.B package
Create the final Debian package.
.TP
.B clean
Remove temporary files.
.TP
.B status
Show current state.
.TP
.B debug
Display debug information.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --help
Show help information.
.SH SEE ALSO
debforge-build(1), debforge-package(1)
